<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 6:00PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Fayette and
eastern Coweta Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 600 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Peachtree City, or 7
miles west of Fayetteville. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Peachtree City, Tyrone, Senoia, Brooks, Sharpsburg,
Turin, Starrs Mill and Sandy Creek.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
